obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (16964)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16964&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 12th October, 1987, vide notification No. S.O. 898(E), dated 12th October, 1987, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (16965)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of National Dairy Development Board as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16965&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects of the National Dairy Development Board at Anand in the State of`
  line `Gujarat are such as to make the institution one of national importance, it is hereby declared that the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (16966)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16966&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Board of Directors of the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(d) "Companies Act" means the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(e) "director" means a director of the National Dairy Development Board, and includes the`
  line Chairman;
  line
  line `(f) "foodstuffs" means such of the foodstuffs as are included in the definition of`
  line `essential commodities as contained in clause (a) of section 2 of the Essential Commodities`
  line `Act, 1955 (10 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(g) "Indian Dairy Corporation" means the Indian Dairy Corporation, a company formed and`
  line `registered under the Companies Act, and having its registered office at Baroda in the State of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(h) "milk product" means--`
  line
  line `(i) sterilised, standardised, recombined, toned, double-toned, skimmed, flavoured or acidified`
  line milk;
  line
  line `(ii) ice-cream;`
  line
  line `(iii) cream;`
  line
  line `(iv) cheese;`
  line
  line `(v) butter;`
  line
  line `(vi) milk powders;`
  line
  line `(vii) weaning foods with milk and infant milk foods;`
  line
  line `(viii) malted milk foods with or without cocoa powder;`
  line
  line `(ix) ghee;`
  line
  line `(x) anhydrous milk fat and butter oil;`
  line
  line `(xi) casein;`
  line
  line `(xii) any other product containing milk or all or any of the milk products specified above`
  line `which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(i) "National Dairy Development Board" means the National Dairy Development Board`
  line `incorporated under section 4;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "restructuring and streamlining", in relation to the organisational and functional set-up of the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) opening or closing of units or offices;`
  line
  line `(ii) revision of the organisational and functional set-up;`
  line
  line `(iii) declaration of staff required;`
  line
  line `(iv) integration of posts, fixation of seniority and pay scales;`
  line
  line `(v) integration of required personnel in the revised set-up and issuance of appointment orders`
  line `in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(vi) declaration or demarcation of duties and responsibilities attendant to posts;`
  line
  line `(vii) declaration of posts equivalent to one another; and`
  line
  line `(viii) any other matter that may be necessary of incidental to meet the organisational or`
  line `functional needs of the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(l) "society" means the National Dairy Development Board, a society formed and registered`
  line `under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) and functioning as such immediately before`
  line `the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(m) words and expressions used herein and not defined, but defined in the Companies Act, have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (16967)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of National Dairy Development Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16967&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Dairy Development`
  line `Board is hereby constituted a body corporate by the same name, and as such body corporate, it shall have`
  line `perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold`
  line `and dispose of property and to contract, and shall, by that name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the National Dairy Development Board shall be at Anand in the State of`
  line Gujarat.
  line
  line `(3) The National Dairy Development Board may establish units, offices, branches or agencies at any`
  line `such place in or outside India as it may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (16968)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Vesting of undertakings of Indian Dairy Corporation in National Dairy Development Board and dissolution of Indian Dairy Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16968&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act, all the undertakings of the Indian Dairy Corporation shall stand transferred to and`
  line `vest in the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, the Indian Dairy Corporation shall, on`
  line `and from the appointed day, stand dissolved by virtue of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (16969)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Effect of incorporation of National Dairy Development Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16969&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed`
  line day,--
  line
  line `(a) all properties and assets, movable and immovable, of, or belonging to, the society and the`
  line `Indian Dairy Corporation (hereinafter referred to as the dissolved company) shall vest in the National`
  line `Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(b) all the rights, debts, liabilities, interests, privileges and obligations of the society and the`
  line `Indian Dairy Corporation shall stand transferred to, and be the rights, liabilities, interests, privileges`
  line `and obligations of, the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(c) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (b), all debts, liabilities and obligations incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for, the society or`
  line `the dissolved company, immediately before the appointed day for or in connection with their`
  line `purposes, shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into, or engaged to be done by, with or for,`
  line `the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums of money due to the society and the dissolved company, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, shall be deemed to be due to the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) every subsidiary or the society and the dissolved company shall become the subsidiary of the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(f) every organisation, which was being managed immediately before the appointed day by the`
  line `society or, as the case may be, by the dissolved company, shall be managed by the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board for such period to such extent and in such manner as the circumstances may`
  line require;
  line
  line `(g) every organisation which was getting financial, managerial or technical assistance from the`
  line `society or the dissolved company, immediately before the appointed day, may continue to be given`
  line `financial, managerial or technical assistance, as the case may be, by the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board, for such period, to such extent and in such manner as the National Dairy Development Board`
  line `may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(h) the amount representing the capital of the dissolved company shall form part of the funds of`
  line `the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(i) any reference to the society or, as the case may be, to the dissolved company, in any law other`
  line `than this Act or in any contract or other instrument, shall be deemed to be reference to the National`
  line `Dairy Development Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (16970)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Saving of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16970&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If, on the appointed day, there is pending any suit, arbitration,`
  line `appeal or other legal proceedings of whatever nature by or against the society or the dissolved company,`
  line `the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason of the`
  line `incorporation of the National Dairy Development Board under section 4 or dissolution of the Indian Dairy`
  line `Corporation under section 5, as the case may be, but the suit, arbitration, appeal or other proceedings may`
  line `be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the National Dairy Development Board in the same`
  line `manner and to the same extent as it would or may have been continued, prosecuted and enforced by or`
  line `against the society or the dissolved company, as the case may be, if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (16971)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Management of National Dairy Development Board and composition of its Board of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16971&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction, control and management of the affairs and`
  line `business of the National Dairy Development Board shall vest in a Board of Directors, which shall`
  line `exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Directors of the National Dairy Development Board shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) one director from amongst the officials of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) two directors from amongst the Chairmen of the State Co-operative Dairy Federations;`
  line
  line `(d) whole-time directors, not more than three in number, from amongst the executives of the`
  line `highest grade of the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(e) one director, being an expert, from outside the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman and the director referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) shall be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government and the directors referred to in clauses (c), (d) and (e) of sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government after consultation with the Chairman:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman and the director referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `persons professionally qualified in one or more specialities, namely, dairying, animal husbandry, rural`
  line `economics, rural development, business administration or banking.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may associate with itself, in such manner, on such terms and for such purposes as it`
  line `may deem fit, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the`
  line `Board relevant to the purposes for which he has been associated but shall not have the right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (16972)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Terms of office and conditions of service, etc., of Chairman and directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16972&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman`
  line `shall be the Chief Executive of the National Dairy Development Board and shall hold office for such`
  line `period as the Central Government may determine and any person so nominated shall be eligible for`
  line renomination.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the services of the Chairman, at any time before the expiry of the period determined`
  line `under that sub-section, by giving him notice of not less than three months in writing or three months`
  line `salary and allowances in lieu thereof, and the Chairman shall also have the right to relinquish his office, at`
  line `any time before the expiry of the period specified under that sub-section, by giving to the Central`
  line `Government notice of not less than three months in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman shall receive such salary and allowances as may be determined by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) Where an executive of the National Dairy Development Board has been nominated under section`
  line `8 as a whole-time director thereof, such nomination shall be without prejudice to his continuance as an`
  line `executive of the National Dairy Development Board and he may be continued as such executive on his`
  line `ceasing to be a director.`
  line
  line `(5) The directors nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 8 shall hold office for such`
  line `period not exceeding one year at a time as the Central Government may determine, and the directors`
  line `nominated under clauses (d) and (e) of sub-section (2) of section 8 shall hold office for such period as the`
  line `Central Government may determine.`
  line
  line `(6) Every director, other than the Chairman, shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(7) The directors referred to in clauses (b), (c) and (e) of sub-section (2) of section 8 shall be paid`
  line `such allowances as the Central Government may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (16973)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16973&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at the head office of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board or any of its offices at such times as the Chairman may direct, and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its`
  line `meetings) as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman or, if he is unable to attend a meeting of the Board, any other director nominated by`
  line `the Chairman in this behalf and, in the absence of such nomination or where there is no Chairman, any`
  line `director chosen by the directors present from among themselves, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the directors present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman or the`
  line `person presiding shall have the right to exercise a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (3), every director of the Board shall have one vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (16974)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Manner of transacting business of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16974&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board`
  line `shall, in the discharge of its functions, act on sound business principles with due regard to public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise prescribed, the Chairman shall have the powers of general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the National Dairy Development Board,`
  line `and he may exercise all other powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman may, when he is unable to discharge his functions by reason of his being away or`
  line `otherwise, authorise any whole-time director to discharge all or any of his functions for a temporary`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) In the absence of the Chairman and of an authorised whole-time director as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3), for whatsoever reason, the powers of the Chairman may be exercised by the senior-most`
  line `of the whole-time directors referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (16975)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Management committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16975&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may from time to time constitute such number of`
  line `management committees as it may deem fit for the purpose of assisting the Board in the efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) A management committee shall consist of such number of persons (whether directors or`
  line `otherwise) as its members as the Board may determine, subject to the condition that in every such`
  line `committee either the Chairman or a whole-time director shall be a member thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Every management committee shall function under the general control, direction and`
  line `superintendence of the Board, and for such duration and in such manner as the Board may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) The minutes of every meeting of the management committees shall, as soon as may be, be laid`
  line `before the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (16976)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Allowances, etc., of members of management committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16976&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of any`
  line `management committee, other than the Chairman and whole-time directors, may be paid such allowances,`
  line `if any, as may be prescribed, for attending the meetings of the management committee or for attending to`
  line `any other work of the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All other matters pertaining to the conduct of proceedings of the management committees shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (16977)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Delegation of powers to management committees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16977&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may delegate to any`
  line `management committee or to any member thereof or to any officer of the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified by the Board, such of its`
  line `powers and functions under this Act as it may deem necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, if it considers it necessary so to do in the public interest, delegate any of its`
  line `powers and functions, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified by it, to a`
  line `co-operative federation at the National or State level, or to any organisation owned, managed, controlled`
  line `or assisted by the National Dairy Development Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (16978)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Delegation of powers to whole-time directors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16978&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, from time to time, by`
  line `order, delegate, subject to such general and special conditions as it may deem fit to impose, the powers of`
  line `appointment, termination, suspension and dismissal from service of any employee of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) who is drawing a salary in such higher grade as may be prescribed, to a whole-time director,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) who is drawing a salary in any grade, other than a higher grade prescribed under clause (a), to`
  line `such officer of the National Dairy Development Board as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to employees falling under clause (b), the Chairman may, if he considers it`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, perform the functions of the Board under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (16979)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Powers and functions of National Dairy Development Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16979&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall be the duty and function of the National Dairy Development Board to promote plan`
  line `and organise programmes for the purposes of development of dairy and other agriculture based and`
  line `allied industries and biologicals on an intensive and nation-wide basis and to render assistance in the`
  line `implementation of such programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) it shall be the responsibility of the National Dairy Development Board to adopt the`
  line `co-operative strategy in a more effective manner on an intensive and nation-wide basis and to take`
  line `such steps as may be necessary for the purposes aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `(c) the National Dairy Development Board may take such measures for carrying out the said`
  line `purposes, and for the exercise of its powers and the performance of its functions and responsibilities`
  line `under this Act, as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the measures`
  line `referred to therein may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) facilitating research and promotional activities in the fields of dairying, immunology, animal`
  line `husbandry, agriculture and horticulture;`
  line
  line `(b) imparting technological know-how to such organisations in the co-operative or public sector`
  line `as are engaged in the production, procurement, preservation or marketing of milk and milk products;`
  line
  line `(c) facilitating the training of personnel for absorbing and utilising the technical know-how that`
  line `may be imparted;`
  line
  line `(d) designing, planning, promoting developing, constructing, sponsoring and setting up of dairy`
  line `industries and undertaking any other related promotional activity including the financing of the same;`
  line
  line `(e) providing consultancy and managerial services and the execution of any project on a turn-key`
  line `basis or otherwise, furnishing integral services such as storage, transportation, processing, distribution`
  line `of milk and milk products and to serve as a lead institution with reference to milk and milk products;`
  line
  line `(f) adopting such measures as may be practicable--`
  line
  line `(i) for the conservation of milk and milk products by avoidance of waste at all stages or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(ii) to assist primary producers of milk and milk products and persons in the co-operative and`
  line `public sector to get incentive prices; and`
  line
  line `(iii) to build up a national milk grid;`
  line
  line `(g) recommending to Government, as and when necessary, the maximum and minimum prices to`
  line `be fixed for the purchase or sale of milk and, if so required, assist in the enforcement of it;`
  line
  line `(h) functioning as a channelising agency in respect of import and export of milk and milk`
  line `products and of milch animals or bulls;`
  line
  line `(i) providing financial, technical, administrative, managerial or other assistance or taking such`
  line `measures as may be necessary--`
  line
  line `(A) for the development (if required by the import of quality semen) and preservation of high`
  line `yielding cattle;`
  line
  line `(B) for adopting improved methods of cattle breeding;`
  line
  line `(C) for increasing production and supply of better and improved animal feed including`
  line `fodder; and`
  line
  line `(D) generally for the enhancement of the cattle wealth of the country;`
  line
  line `(j) processing, promoting or financing technological, industrial or economic research in milk and`
  line `milk products in such manner as the Board may deem fit by the utilisation of available institutions or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(k) financing, in such manner as the Board may deem appropriate (including contribution to`
  line `capital), of co-operative federations, co-operative unions or co-operative enterprises or of any scheme`
  line `in the co-operative or public sector intended to stimulate the production, preservation, distribution`
  line `and consumption of milk and milk products nation-wide;`
  line
  line `(l) regulating the dairy and allied industries and functioning as regulatory authority therefor, as`
  line `may be required by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(m) adopting measures for the development and co-ordination of organisations in the production`
  line `of milk and milk products so as to enable the primary producers thereof to become participants in,`
  line `and beneficiaries of, the development and growth of dairy and allied industries;`
  line
  line `(n) collecting and compiling relevant data and statistics necessary for the efficient management of`
  line `the national milk grid and national milch herd and on any other matter relating to dairying and allied`
  line industries;
  line
  line `(o) promoting publicity on the research and development of dairy and allied industries;`
  line
  line `(p) promoting and developing production, grading and marketing of milk and milk products in`
  line `various parts of the country;`
  line
  line `(q) co-operating with international organisations and foreign experts and for functioning as the`
  line `agent of the Central Government for the reception, utilisation and disbursement of any gift of milk`
  line `and milk products and any other foodstuffs;`
  line
  line `(r) building up of a reserve of buffer stock of basic commodities;`
  line
  line `(s) promoting the export of milk and milk products where, in the opinion of the Board, it is so`
  line `required to avoid waste or to otherwise serve the public interest and generally for exporting any`
  line `article produced, processed or promoted by it;`
  line
  line `(t) acquiring, holding and disposing of any property for the purposes of its business;`
  line
  line `(u) transferring the whole or any part of its managerial, technical or other functions in relation to`
  line `any organisations receiving assistance from the National Dairy Development Board to the recipient`
  line organisation;
  line
  line `(v) advancing or lending money upon security of movable or immovable property or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(w) borrowing money in such manner and upon such security as the Board may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(x) carrying on, either by itself or through any other organisations, any other business or class of`
  line `business, in a case where such business or class of business was being carried on by the society or the`
  line `dissolved company immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(y) promoting and encouraging co-operative effort among those engaged in the production of`
  line `milk and milk products and other foodstuffs;`
  line
  line `(z) levying fees or other charges for any assistance given or services rendered by the National`
  line `Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(za) carrying on any other business or doing any other act or thing as may be necessary,`
  line `incidental or conducive to further the objectives of the National Dairy Development Board under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) If, immediately before the appointed day, either the society or the dissolved company`
  line `was engaged in the production, research and development, processing, marketing, import, export`
  line `or other activities, or had been rendering any service or assistance, in relation to any article or`
  line `product, other than milk and milk products or the dairy industry, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or in any other law, the National Dairy Development Board may engage in the`
  line `production, research and development, processing, marketing, import, export or other activities, or render`
  line `such other services or assistance in relation to the said article or product as may be required, and the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to that article or product, as`
  line `if any reference therein to milk and milk products or to dairy and allied industries had been a reference to`
  line `that article or product or service or activity.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Government or the Government of any State considers that, having regard to`
  line `the special expertise of the National Dairy Development Board and the needs of the public, it is necessary`
  line `or advisable to entrust the National Dairy Development Board with any activity, other than that to which`
  line `the foregoing sub-sections apply, it may, entrust such activity to the National Dairy Development Board,`
  line `whereupon it shall be competent for the National Dairy Development Board to carry on such activity.`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, it shall be competent for the National`
  line `Dairy Development Board to participate, with the prior approval of the Central Government, in any other`
  line `organisation, financially, managerially or in any other manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (16980)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Provisions regarding members of board of society and directors of dissolved company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16980&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every person holding office as a member of the board of the society, or as a director of the`
  line `dissolved company, immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from that day, cease to hold`
  line `office as such member or director.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (16981)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Provisions relating to officers and other employees of society and of dissolved company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16981&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 19, every full-time officer or other employee, holding`
  line `office immediately before the appointed day, in the society or the dissolved company, shall, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, become an officer or other employee, as the case may be, of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board and shall hold office or service in the National Dairy Development Board on the`
  line `same terms and conditions of service as he would have had under the society or the dissolved company,`
  line `as the case may be, and shall continue to do so unless and until his terms and conditions of service are`
  line `duly altered by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (16982)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Board to restructure and streamline organisational and functional set-up of National Dairy Development Board to secure utmost efficiency in functioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16982&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Chapter, the National Dairy Development Board may make such orders or take`
  line `such action as may be necessary for restructuring and streamlining the organisational and functional`
  line `set-up of the National Dairy Development Board to secure utmost efficiency in its functioning, and the`
  line `Board shall, for achieving this object, be competent to declare any officer or other employee or any class`
  line `of officers or other employees to be redundant if it finds them redundant by way of being surplus or`
  line `otherwise due to duplication of posts of the same nature, or absence of the special expertise required for`
  line `the post in the revised set-up, or the non-availability of posts in a particular office or unit of the National`
  line `Dairy Development Board and it is not practicable to accommodate him in the type of post in the`
  line `particular grade.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Chapter shall preclude the Board, if it is considered necessary for the purpose of`
  line `rationalising the conditions of service of the officers and other employees so transferred to it, to change`
  line `their designation, conditions of service or the scales of pay applicable to them or to reallocate their duties`
  line `and functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (16983)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Schemes regarding compensation to redundant employees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16983&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The officers or other`
  line `employees declared as redundant in pursuance of section 19, shall be dealt with in accordance with such`
  line `scheme or schemes as the Board may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, make in this`
  line `behalf and different schemes may be made in relation to different classes or categories of officers and`
  line `other employees.`
  line
  line `(2) The scheme or schemes referred to in sub-section (1) may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the quantum of compensation payable to any officer or other employee referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) and the mode of payment thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that the compensation so payable shall in no case be less than that payable to him under`
  line `the service conditions applicable to him if his services were dispensed with;`
  line
  line `(b) the quantum of arrears of salary or other emoluments, provident fund, gratuity or any other`
  line `amount that may be payable in accordance with the service conditions applicable to them;`
  line
  line `(c) the provision for appeal for the aggrieved redundant officers and other employees and for the`
  line `appellate authority, being an officer not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the Government of`
  line `India in the Ministry dealing with Agriculture;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter pertaining to the termination of service consequent on their being declared`
  line redundant.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (16984)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Compensation for transfer of employees not payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16984&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The transfer of the services of any`
  line `officer or other employee of the society or of the dissolved company to the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board shall not entitle any such officer or other employee to any compensation under the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or any other law for the time being in force, and no such claim shall be`
  line `entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (16985)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Provident fund, gratuity, welfare and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16985&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a provident fund has been`
  line `established by the society or the dissolved company in respect of either of them for the benefit of the`
  line `officers or other employees and the same stands vested in a trust, the moneys and other assets standing to`
  line `the credit of each provident fund shall continue to be held in trust with the same objects as were`
  line `applicable before the appointed day and the trustees of such trusts immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall, subject to the provisions of the trust deeds and the rules relating to the respective trusts, continue to`
  line `function as trustees in respect of the respective provident fund until and unless otherwise directed by the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board, and the rights relating to the said trusts shall, as from the appointed`
  line `day, vest in the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any gratuity, welfare or other fund had been established by the society or the dissolved`
  line `company for the benefit of its officers or other employees and is in existence immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, all moneys and other assets standing to the credit of or relatable to such gratuity, welfare`
  line `or other fund shall vest in the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Board may give such`
  line `directions relating to the trusts or funds or take such other action as it may deem fit so as to bring about`
  line `uniformity or to effect integration in part or in whole in such trusts or funds.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may, having regard to the welfare of the officers and other employees or their families,`
  line `take such steps for the advancement of their health, education or other interests as may be prescribed and`
  line `create such institutions as may be required for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this section shall derogate the power of the Board to make`
  line `regulations for establishing or maintaining any provident fund, welfare fund, gratuity fund or other fund`
  line `for any of its officers or other employees.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (16986)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Borrowing powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16986&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government or in accordance with the terms of any general or special authority given to it by the Central`
  line `Government, borrow money from any source as it may deem fit for discharging all or any of its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (16987)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16987&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the National Dairy Development Board by`
  line `way of grants or loans such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (16988)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Grants, donations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16988&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The National Dairy Development Board may receive gifts, grants,`
  line `donations or benefactions from Government or any other source in or outside India and the same shall be`
  line `used by the Board for exercising its functions and discharging its responsibilities under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Dairy Development Board shall not receive any gifts, grants, donations or`
  line `benefactions from a foreign government or any other source outside India except with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (16989)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `National Dairy Development Board Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16989&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Dairy Development Board shall`
  line `maintain a Fund to be called the National Dairy Development Board Fund to which shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money vested in the National Dairy Development Board under Chapter II;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums of money that may be provided by Government;`
  line
  line `(c) all fees and other charges received by the National Dairy Development Board;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums of money generated from gift commodities by the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board or received by it by way of grants, donations, benefactions, bequests or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(e) all sums of money received by the National Dairy Development Board in any other manner or`
  line `from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All sums of money credited to the said Fund shall, subject to the regulations, if any, made in this`
  line `behalf, be deposited with the State Bank of India or any other nationalised bank.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In sub-section "nationalised bank" means a corresponding new bank as defined in the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) and the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (44 of 1980).`
  line
  line `(3) The said Fund shall be applied towards meeting the administrative and other expenses of the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board, including expenses incurred in the exercise of the powers and the`
  line `discharge of its functions and responsibilities under section 16 or in relation to any of the activities`
  line `referred to therein or for anything relatable thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (16990)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Preparation of accounts and balance-sheet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16990&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board shall be prepared in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the National Dairy Development Board to be`
  line `closed and balanced as on the 31st day of March each year or such other date as the Board may, with the`
  line `concurrence of the Central Government, decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (16991)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16991&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the National Dairy Development Board shall be audited by auditors`
  line `duly qualified to act as auditors of companies under the Companies Act, and the appointment of auditors`
  line `and remuneration payable to them shall be subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every auditor in the performance of his duties shall have at all reasonable times access to books,`
  line `accounts and other documents of the National Dairy Development Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors shall submit their report to the Board which shall forward a copy of their report to`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (16992)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Reports to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16992&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause the report of the`
  line `auditors under section 28 to be laid before both the Houses of Parliament as soon as may be after such`
  line `report is received by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (16993)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16993&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any agreement to the contrary, the Board may, by notice in writing, require any person to which the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board or the society or the dissolved company has granted any loan or`
  line `advance, to discharge forthwith in full, its liabilities to the Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Board that any false or misleading information in any material particular`
  line `was given in the application for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person has failed to comply with the terms of its contract in the matter of the loan or`
  line `advance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the person is unable to pay his debts or that`
  line `proceedings for liquidation may be commenced in respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned as security for the loan or`
  line `advance is not insured and kept insured by the person to the satisfaction of the Board (or depreciates`
  line `in value to such an extent that, in the opinion of the Board, further security to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Board should be given and such security is not given after demand); or`
  line
  line `(e) if, without due permission, any machinery, plant or other equipment (whether forming part of`
  line `security or not) is removed from the concerned premises without being replaced; or`
  line
  line `(f) if it appears to the Board that any condition in the loan agreement relating to the supply of`
  line `goods or implementation of the project is being substantially violated; or`
  line
  line `(g) if, for any other reason, the Board considers it necessary so to do for protecting the interests of`
  line `the National Dairy Development Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (16994)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Special provisions for enforcement of claims by National Dairy Development Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16994&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person, in breach of any agreement, makes any default in the repayment of any`
  line `loan or advance or any instalment thereof (or in meeting its obligations in relation to the guarantee given`
  line `by the National Dairy Development Board) or otherwise fails to comply with the terms of agreement with`
  line `the Board or where the Board requires any person to make immediate repayment of any loan or advance`
  line `under section 30 and the person fails to make such repayment, then, without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 69 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), any officer of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board, generally or specially authorised by the Board in this behalf, may apply to the court`
  line `for one or more of the following reliefs, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for an order for the sale of the property pledged, mortgaged, hypothecated or assigned to the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board as security for the loan or advance; or`
  line
  line `(b) for transferring the management of any organisation to the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) for an ad interim injunction where there is apprehension that the machinery or other`
  line `equipment is being removed from the premises of the organisation without due permission.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for making an application under sub-section (1) and for the disposal thereof shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (16995)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Defects in appointments not to invalidate acts, etc., of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16995&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Board or of any committee of the National Dairy Development Board shall be questioned on the ground`
  line `merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board or the committee, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (16996)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of acts done in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16996&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board or any director or any officer or other employee of the Board or any`
  line `other person authorised by the Board to discharge any functions under this Act, for any loss or damage`
  line `caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or of any other law or provision having the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (16997)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16997&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every director shall be indemnified by the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board against all losses and expenses incurred by him, in, or in relation to, the discharge of`
  line `his duties, except such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (16998)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16998&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall not, except as otherwise required by`
  line `this Act or any other law, divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs of, the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board or of the society or of the dissolved company except in circumstances in which it is`
  line `in accordance with the law or practice and usage customary among financial institutions, necessary or`
  line `appropriate for the Board to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director, member of a committee, auditor or officer or other employee of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in`
  line `the form set out in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (16999)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Recruitment of additional officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=16999&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in Chapter V`
  line `shall be deemed to prejudice the right of the National Dairy Development Board to create such number of`
  line `additional posts or to appoint such number of additional officers or other employees as it may consider`
  line `necessary or desirable for the efficient discharge of the functions of the National Dairy Development`
  line `Board and where any such officer or other employee is appointed, the terms and conditions of service,`
  line `including inter se seniority, may also be determined by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (17000)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Liquidation only under orders of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17000&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No provision of any law relating to`
  line `the winding up of companies or corporations shall apply to the National Dairy Development Board and it`
  line `shall not be placed in liquidation save by an order of the Central Government and in such manner as it`
  line `may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (17001)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Delegation of certain powers by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17001&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, on`
  line `the recommendation of the National Dairy Development Board, if satisfied that it is necessary so to do in`
  line `the public interest, make any scheme for the purpose of enabling the National Dairy Development Board`
  line `to undertake and perform any of the activities or functions of the Central Government relatable to dairy,`
  line `foodstuffs and connected industries, particularly with reference to matters related to the development of`
  line `the national milk grid by the regulation of the production, procurement, marketing, export-import,`
  line `maintenance of standards or such like activities (including the collection and compilation of statistics and`
  line `relevant data).`
  line
  line `(2) Every scheme made under sub-section (1) shall be published in the Official Gazette and may`
  line `contain such conditions, restrictions or limitations as the Central Government may deem fit to impose.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (17002)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Transitional provisions for auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17002&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any auditor appointed in relation to the society or the`
  line `dissolved company, functioning immediately before the appointed day, may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, be continued by the National Dairy Development Board for such period and on`
  line `such terms as may be considered necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (17003)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Transitional provisions with regard to Chairman and Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17003&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman of the society,`
  line `holding office immediately before the appointed day, shall be the Chairman of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board until a Chairman is nominated in accordance with the provisions of this Act and he`
  line `shall be competent to perform the functions of the Board until the constitution of the Board under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (17004)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Management or assistance to others to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17004&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is hereby`
  line `declared that where, before the appointed day, either the society or the dissolved company was managing`
  line `any other organisation or rendering any technical or other assistance to any organisation or person, the`
  line `National Dairy Development Board may continue to render the same or similar service to such extent, for`
  line `such period and with such modifications as the Board may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (17005)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Mother Dairy to be a subsidiary unit of National Dairy Development Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17005&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line The
  line `undertaking known as the Mother Dairy, Delhi, shall, on and from the appointed day, become a`
  line `subsidiary unit of the National Dairy Development Board but shall retain its separate character, unless`
  line `otherwise decided by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (17006)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Formation of companies with previous approval of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17006&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Board considers it necessary so to do, for the implementation of any of its objectives, it may, subject to`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government form one or more companies either by itself or in`
  line `conjunction with any of its subsidiaries or with any other undertaking.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any company has been formed in pursuance of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a company formed by the Board by itself or along with its subsidiaries, it may`
  line `contribute such capital, transfer such of its assets or render such assistance, as may be required, so as`
  line `to enable the company so formed to function; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, it may contribute capital, transfer assets or render assistance in such manner`
  line `and to such extent as the Board may deem fit subject to specific previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government in that regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (17007)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title Omitted
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17007&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `[Exemption from tax on income] Omitted by Act 20 of 2002 (20 of 2002) s.162`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (17013)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17013&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The National Dairy Development Board shall furnish, from time to time, to the`
  line `Central Government such returns as the Central Government may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (17014)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to make schemes and regulations regarding service matters retrospectively.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17014&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `scheme or regulation made under this Act in relation to conditions of service or like matters of officers or`
  line `other employees of the National Dairy Development Board, may be made retrospectively from any date`
  line `not earlier than the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (17015)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17015&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in the Companies Act, the Industrial Disputes`
  line `Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument having effect by`
  line `virtue of any law other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (17016)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17016&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by notification in the Gazette of India, make`
  line `regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the schemes made thereunder, to provide`
  line `for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed for the transaction of business at the meetings of the Board and`
  line `the number of members which shall form quorum at a meeting under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the allowances to be paid to the members of any management committee, other than the`
  line `Chairman and whole-time directors, for attending the meetings of the management committee or for`
  line `attending to any other work of the National Dairy Development Board under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13 and the other matters pertaining to the conduct of proceedings of the management`
  line `committees under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(c) the higher grade for the purposes of clause (a) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the particulars of the steps for the advancement of the health, education or other interests of`
  line `the officers and other employees or their families as referred to in sub-section (4) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(e) the matters of detail regarding establishment or maintenance of funds referred to in`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions subject to which sums of money are to be deposited under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner in which the balance-sheet and accounts of the National Dairy`
  line `Development Board shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for making an application under sub-section (1) of section 31 and for the`
  line `disposal thereof under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(i) conditions of service of officers and other employees;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (17017)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17017&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of five years from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (17018)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Schemes and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001&sectionId=17018&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00003_198737_1517807323001
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Every scheme and every regulation`
  line `made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and, if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or`
  line `the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the scheme or`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the scheme or regulation should not be made, the scheme or`
  line `regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that scheme or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
